All the racial choices are fine.  Frail SKs (Dark elves, gnomes, erudites) play rather differently from medium (human, iksar) or fatty (ogre, troll) but all do reasonably well, given decent player skill.

+STR items and buffs, plus , weight reducer bags are fairly easily obtained, even at quite low level and without huge cash resources.  For the truly new character, decent starting armour quests are available for erudites, as well as humans, dark elves and gnomes.

NB - for initial stats, ensure your AGI is above 75, unless you can affor good +AGI gear, and consider putting points into STA instead of STR - it'll be harder to max that out later on.

So, pick the race you like, and ignore the morons who say otherwise.

